{
  "document_id": "ps-78",
  "title": "Psalms 78",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Give ear, O my people, to my teaching;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "I will open my mouth in a parable;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "things that we have heard and known,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "We will not hide them from their children;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "He established a decree in Jacob"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "that the next generation might know them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "so that they should set their hope in God,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "and that they should not be like their ancestors,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "The Ephraimites, armed with the bow,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "They did not keep God’s covenant"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "They forgot what he had done"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "In the sight of their ancestors he worked marvels"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "He divided the sea and let them pass through it"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "In the daytime he led them with a cloud"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "He split rocks open in the wilderness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "He made streams come out of the rock"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Yet they sinned still more against him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "They tested God in their heart"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "They spoke against God, saying,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Even though he struck the rock so that water gushed out"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "Therefore, when the Lord heard, he was full of rage;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "because they had no faith in God"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "Yet he commanded the skies above"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "he rained down on them manna to eat"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "Mortals ate of the bread of angels;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "He caused the east wind to blow in the heavens,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "he rained flesh upon them like dust,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "he let them fall within their camp,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "And they ate and were well filled,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-30",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 30,
      "text": "But before they had satisfied their craving,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-31",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 31,
      "text": "the anger of God rose against them,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-32",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 32,
      "text": "In spite of all this they still sinned;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-33",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 33,
      "text": "So he made their days vanish like a breath"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-34",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 34,
      "text": "When he killed them, they searched for him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-35",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 35,
      "text": "They remembered that God was their rock,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-36",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 36,
      "text": "But they flattered him with their mouths;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-37",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 37,
      "text": "Their heart was not steadfast toward him;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-38",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 38,
      "text": "Yet he, being compassionate,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-39",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 39,
      "text": "He remembered that they were but flesh,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-40",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 40,
      "text": "How often they rebelled against him in the wilderness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-41",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 41,
      "text": "They tested God again and again"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-42",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 42,
      "text": "They did not keep in mind his power"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-43",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 43,
      "text": "when he displayed his signs in Egypt"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-44",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 44,
      "text": "He turned their rivers to blood,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-45",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 45,
      "text": "He sent among them swarms of flies that devoured them"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-46",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 46,
      "text": "He gave their crops to the caterpillar"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-47",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 47,
      "text": "He destroyed their vines with hail"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-48",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 48,
      "text": "He gave over their cattle to the hail"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-49",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 49,
      "text": "He let loose on them his fierce anger,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-50",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 50,
      "text": "He made a path for his anger;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-51",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 51,
      "text": "He struck all the firstborn in Egypt,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-52",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 52,
      "text": "Then he led out his people like sheep"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-53",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 53,
      "text": "He led them in safety so that they were not afraid,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-54",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 54,
      "text": "And he brought them to his holy hill,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-55",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 55,
      "text": "He drove out nations before them;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-56",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 56,
      "text": "Yet they tested the Most High God"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-57",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 57,
      "text": "but turned away and were faithless like their ancestors;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-58",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 58,
      "text": "For they provoked him to anger with their high places;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-59",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 59,
      "text": "When God heard, he was full of wrath,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-60",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 60,
      "text": "He abandoned his dwelling at Shiloh,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-61",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 61,
      "text": "and delivered his power to captivity,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-62",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 62,
      "text": "He gave his people to the sword"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-63",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 63,
      "text": "Fire devoured their young men,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-64",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 64,
      "text": "Their priests fell by the sword,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-65",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 65,
      "text": "Then the Lord awoke as from sleep,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-66",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 66,
      "text": "He put his adversaries to rout;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-67",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 67,
      "text": "He rejected the tent of Joseph;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-68",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 68,
      "text": "but he chose the tribe of Judah,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-69",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 69,
      "text": "He built his sanctuary like the high heavens,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-70",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 70,
      "text": "He chose his servant David"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-71",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 71,
      "text": "from tending the nursing ewes he brought him"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "ps-78-72",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 72,
      "text": "With upright heart he tended them"
    }
  ]
}